paperparcel

Annotation Type PaperParcel


  • @Documented
 @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Target(value=TYPE)
public @interface PaperParcel

    Annotates Parcelable classes to automatically generate the Parcelable.Creator and writeToParcel boilerplate code that is required as a part of the Parcelable contract. The generated code will be contained in a class with the name of the type annotated with @PaperParcel prepended with PaperParcel. For example, annotating a class named MyModel will produce a class named PaperParcelMyModel. PaperParcelMyModel will have a static field named CREATOR which can be added to your model class. Finally, PaperParcelMyModel will include a static method named writeToParcel which you can call from MyModel#writeToParcel.

    For example: 

    
   @PaperParcel
   class User {
     public static final Parcelable.Creator<User> CREATOR = PaperParcelUser.CREATOR;

     long id;
     String firstName;
     String lastName;

     @Override
     public void writeToParcel(Parcel dest, int flags) {
       PaperParcelUser.writeToParcel(this, dest, flags);
     }

     @Override
     public int describeContents() {
       return 0;
     }
   }
